latestIgtvVideos.caption: With summer here, many people are planning their upcoming vacations. Packing can be overwhelming and stressful, so @markthebarber is sharing his top 5 travel essentials to help. We hope the GilletteLabs with Exfoliating Bar and his other must-haves prepare you for your next getaway. #yourgillettebarber #gillettepartner

@raysantos believes “Spring cleaning” isn’t just meant for your home or workplace. It’s also a great time to upgrade your look and freshen up your skincare routine.
One must-add tool for anyone considering freshening up their routine is the GilletteLabs with Exfoliating Bar. This razor features a unique built-in exfoliation bar that clears dirt and debris before the blades pass so your skin is primed for an amazing shave. Incorporating exfoliation is an easy way to elevate your routine and achieve cleaner, fresher skin! #GillettePartner

Thanks for the effortless post @iamdavidfalla! Wedding season is upon us, and it’s important to look your best for that special day. Whether you’re attending the wedding, standing up or getting married yourself, you need to consider your whole look, which includes both hair style and facial hair. One way to easily shave and exfoliate at the same time is with the GilletteLabs with Exfoliating Bar. It’ll leave you with a fresh, clean look for your big day! #gillettepartner

latestIgtvVideos.title: Handle With Care | Gillette TREO-First Razor Designed to Shave Someone Else
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
There have been over 4,000 razors designed for shaving yourself. None have been specifically designed to shave someone else – until now. 
Gillette TREO is the first of its kind, a unique razor we designed for caregivers to confidently shave their loved ones. 
Learn more and purchase at Gillette.com/TREO

Look good, feel good, play good. #Ad #GillettePartner
30 years ago, my dad handed me my first @Gillette razor and those were the words he lived by. He taught me that how you show up (on and off the field) matters. Grooming wasn’t just about appearances, it was about having the confidence to show up as your best, win or lose. 
Today, as a father myself, I pass that same lesson down. It’s not just about shaving — it’s about preparing to show up as your best self every single day. 
Thanks to @Gillette for helping me carry on the tradition. Because when you look sharp, you play sharp. Happy Father’s Day to the ones who taught us how to show up.
